By Chimezie Godfrey President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with family, friends and associates mourning the death of former Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Mustapha Balogun. This was revealed in a statement signed by the Special Adviser to the President on Media & Publicity, Femi Adesina. Buhari also mourns with the Nigeria Police Force, an institution Balogun spent the better part of his life serving. The President recalled that Tafa Balogun, during his tenure as IGP, did his utmost to ensure that the police performed its statutory responsibilities under a democratic dispensation; and his penchant for boosting the morale of officers and men in the Force has been acknowledged by those who served under him. President Buhariâ€™s thoughts are with the family, the government and people of Osun State, as well as colleagues and former colleagues of the deceased police chief. He prayed for the peaceful repose of the soul of the departed.